<chapter xml:id="ch_optics" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Geometric Optics</title>
	<introduction>
    <p> In this chapter you will learn how to model light.</p>
	
	</introduction>
		
    <objectives>
      
      <introduction><p>After successful completion of this chapter, you will be able to:</p></introduction>
		<ol>
			<li><p>Draw ray diagrams using the Ray Model for Light.</p></li>
			<li><p>Explain how light is reflected and refracted upon hitting a surface or entering a medium.</p></li>
			<li><p>Apply the law of refraction to determine how light travels through different mediums.</p></li>
			<li><p>Explain how images are produced by flat and curved mirrors.</p></li>
			<li><p>Explain how lenses work.</p></li>
			<li><p>Differentiate between the wave and ray models for light, and explain in what cases they are most useful.</p></li>
		</ol>
	</objectives>

